{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff5d7c30-e853-4e95-b23a-da54dbac1a68","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, the SDK exclusively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the newer runner) and **no longer emits the VSTest adapter/infrastructure**. That's why `vstest.console` can't discover your tests — the necessary VSTest adapters aren't in the output anymore.\n\n### Your options:\n\n1. **Switch your CI to the new runner** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # works out of the box with the new platform\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   Or, if you truly need `vstest.console`, add the VSTest bridge:\n   ```xml\n   <ItemGroup>\n     <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge\" />\n   </ItemGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Pin to 3.x** until you can migrate your pipeline:\n   ```xml\n   <Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n   ```\n\nThe recommended path forward is option 1 — use `dotnet test` with the built-in Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, which is what MSTest.Sdk 4.x is designed around.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3dc52fe9-7b89-4a7a-8c48-647b2d8d0821","outputTokens":385,"requestId":"4809:286947:615319E:69DB7FC:69FC027C"},"id":"ed1211c5-9050-4586-b5bd-5898d07ee696","timestamp":"2026-05-07T03:09:57.839Z","parentId":"eebdbfd9-ef25-4ead-a267-092c5eb45b06"}
